The boy has his back turned to you, gazing at something you cannot see. "Hello?" you say warily. He doesn't seem to hear you, or chooses to ignore you. "Hello?" you say again, louder this time. The boy finally notices and turns around to look at you. He seems confused, but does not say anything. He nods towards the right, and makes a run for it. You [[follow him]] The cat sits in front of you, licking its paws. "So...here you are. At last." "You...you can talk?" The cat smiles. "But you're a cat!" "Very good. And you're a human. Come with me. I must show you something." [[follow the cat]] [[go back to bed]] You have been walking for what feels like hours. Your bare feet should be cracked and sore by now, but you feel as if you've been walking on thin air. "What's your name, anyway?" "Chester." You stifle a giggle. "Funny name for a cat." Chester ignores you and walks in front. After a few moments, he lets out a breath. "Here it is," he says in awe. The end.He is still running ahead of you. You can hear his breath from here, but you don't know if he's aware that you're following him. Suddenly, something feels strange. Your hands do not feel like yours. The boy abruptly stops. The place where you are now is dark and cold. He points to something up ahead.
